      "message": "Clar: so \"tpm\" should be conceptually \"tpm1\" || \"tpm2\", IIUC.\nIf \"tpm2\" is set iff \"!mocktpm \u0026\u0026 !tast_vm\" case, that\u0027s fine. But, otherwise, switching \"tpm2\" -\u003e \"tpm\" could cause some coverage regression. In case of tpm2 set, are tast_vm and mocktpm always false?",
      "revId": "5fa5e2daac82bcd90fd42ed787a61408f792b45c",
